<section class="section hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-content reveal">
      <h1>{gettext("The language OS for your organization")}</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        {gettext(
          "Glossia captures your voice, terminology, and tone in one place so linguists and teams can shape how your organization speaks across every language and surface."
        )}
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="button primary" href={~p"/interest"}>{gettext("Get started")}</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={~p"/docs"}>{gettext("Check out the docs")}</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-logos">
        <span class="hero-logos-label">{gettext("From builders who worked at")}</span>
        <div class="hero-logos-row">
          <a href="https://soundcloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img src={~p"/assets/logos/soundcloud.svg"} alt="SoundCloud" height="14" />
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.shopify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img src={~p"/assets/logos/shopify.svg"} alt="Shopify" height="26" />
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="geo-accent" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 320" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect
          x="40"
          y="40"
          width="120"
          height="120"
          rx="8"
          stroke="#7c3aed"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          opacity="0.2"
        />
        <rect
          x="100"
          y="100"
          width="120"
          height="120"
          rx="8"
          stroke="#f59e0b"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          opacity="0.15"
        />
        <rect
          x="160"
          y="60"
          width="100"
          height="100"
          rx="8"
          stroke="#059669"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          opacity="0.12"
        />
        <circle cx="80" cy="260" r="30" stroke="#7c3aed" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.1" />
        <circle cx="260" cy="200" r="20" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.1" />
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section community-banner">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="community-banner-content reveal">
      <div class="community-banner-text">
        <h2>{gettext("Join the community")}</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          {gettext(
            "Chat with the team, share feedback, and connect with other builders using Glossia."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        class="button primary community-discord-button"
        href="https://discord.gg/7FRHkwvs"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        <svg
          width="20"
          height="16"
          viewBox="0 0 71 55"
          fill="currentColor"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path d="M60.1 4.9A58.5 58.5 0 0 0 45.4.2a.2.2 0 0 0-.2.1 40.8 40.8 0 0 0-1.8 3.7 54 54 0 0 0-16.2 0A37.4 37.4 0 0 0 25.4.3a.2.2 0 0 0-.2-.1A58.4 58.4 0 0 0 10.5 5a.2.2 0 0 0-.1 0A59.7 59.7 0 0 0 .3 45.3a.3.3 0 0 0 0 .2 58.9 58.9 0 0 0 17.7 9a.2.2 0 0 0 .3-.1 42.1 42.1 0 0 0 3.6-5.9.2.2 0 0 0-.1-.3 38.8 38.8 0 0 1-5.5-2.6.2.2 0 0 1 0-.4l1.1-.9a.2.2 0 0 1 .2 0 42 42 0 0 0 35.8 0 .2.2 0 0 1 .2 0l1.1.9a.2.2 0 0 1 0 .3 36.4 36.4 0 0 1-5.5 2.7.2.2 0 0 0-.1.3 47.2 47.2 0 0 0 3.6 5.9.2.2 0 0 0 .3.1 58.7 58.7 0 0 0 17.7-9 .2.2 0 0 0 .1-.2c1.4-14.8-.3-29.5-10-45.2a.2.2 0 0 0-.1-.1ZM23.7 37.1c-3.9 0-7.1-3.6-7.1-8s3.1-8 7.1-8 7.2 3.6 7.1 8-3.1 8-7.1 8Zm26.2 0c-3.9 0-7.1-3.6-7.1-8s3.1-8 7.1-8 7.2 3.6 7.1 8-3.1 8-7.1 8Z" />
        </svg>
        {gettext("Join our Discord")}
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="how" class="section section-accent">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("How it works")}</h2>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="step-number">01</div>
        <strong>{gettext("Give agents context")}</strong>
        <p>
          {gettext("Add")} <code>GLOSSIA.md</code>
          {gettext(
            "context files alongside your content. Glossia tracks their dependency so when context or content changes, only the affected outputs get regenerated."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="step-number">02</div>
        <strong>{gettext("Choose the best model for the job")}</strong>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Assign different models to different roles and mix providers freely. Glossia acts as a broker between your code and the models, so you don't need to register with each provider separately."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step reveal">
        <div class="step-number">03</div>
        <strong>{gettext("Close the feedback loop")}</strong>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Glossia ships first-party tools for syntax validation and content checks, and you can bring your own. Agents run these tools after each generation and retry on errors, so the loop closes before you even review."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="capabilities" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Two workflows, one tool")}</h2>
    <p class="muted lead reveal">
      {gettext(
        "Whether you need to reach new audiences or sharpen what you already have, the same config file and CLI drives both."
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="tools-grid tools-grid-2col">
      <div class="card tool-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">
          <svg
            width="16"
            height="16"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
          >
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" /><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12" /><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>{gettext("Localize")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Make your content speak new languages. Point Glossia at your source files, list target languages, and it produces localized versions that preserve structure, code blocks, and formatting. Run"
          )}
          <code>glossia translate</code>
          {gettext("and ship to every market.")}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card tool-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">
          <svg
            width="16"
            height="16"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
          >
            <path d="M11 4H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7" /><path d="M18.5 2.5a2.121 2.121 0 0 1 3 3L12 15l-4 1 1-4 9.5-9.5z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>{gettext("Revisit")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Improve your content in place. Glossia reviews source files for clarity, accuracy, and tone using the context you provide. The revised output overwrites the original or writes to a separate path. Run"
          )}
          <code>glossia revisit</code>
          {gettext("to sharpen your docs, guides, or blog posts.")}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="tools" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Closing the loop")}</h2>
    <p class="muted lead reveal">
      {gettext(
        "Agents don't just generate content. They verify it, catch errors, and retry until the output meets your standards."
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="tools-grid">
      <div class="card tool-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <h3>{gettext("Generate")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Agents produce content based on your source files and the context you provide in"
          )} <code>GLOSSIA.md</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card tool-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <h3>{gettext("Verify")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Built-in tools check syntax, structure, and preserved tokens. You can also plug in your own linters, compilers, or validators."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card tool-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <h3>{gettext("Retry")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "When a check fails, agents see the error and try again. The loop repeats until the output is valid or the retry limit is reached."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="config" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Context flows down, config stays close")}</h2>
    <p class="muted lead reveal">
      {gettext(
        "The narrower the scope, the closer to the code. Global defaults live at the root, project-specific rules nest deeper, and shared resources like glossaries live in Glossia so they can be reused across repositories."
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="config-grid">
      <div class="card config-card reveal">
        <h3>GLOSSIA.md</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext("Define content sources, targets, and output patterns in TOML frontmatter.")}
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block"><code>{raw("+++\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token table class-name\">content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token key property\">source</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;site/src/_data/home.json&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"token key property\">targets</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">&quot;es&quot;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;de&quot;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;ko&quot;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;ja&quot;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token key property\">output</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;site/src/_data/i18n/{lang}/{basename}.{ext}&quot;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token table class-name\">content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token key property\">source</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">&quot;docs/guide/*.md&quot;</span>\n+++\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Context for the content agent...</span>")}</code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="card config-card reveal">
        <h3>{gettext("Project layout")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext("Context files nest alongside your content. Language overrides sit next door.")}
        </p>
        <div class="file-tree">
          <ul>
            <li><span class="highlight">GLOSSIA.md</span></li>
            <li>
              <span class="dir">GLOSSIA/</span>
              <ul>
                <li><span class="file">es.md</span></li>
                <li><span class="file">ja.md</span></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="dir">docs/</span>
              <ul>
                <li><span class="highlight">GLOSSIA.md</span></li>
                <li>
                  <span class="dir">GLOSSIA/</span>
                  <ul>
                    <li><span class="file">de.md</span></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <span class="dir">guide/</span>
                  <ul>
                    <li><span class="file">intro.md</span></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="dir">site/</span>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <span class="dir">src/</span>
                  <ul>
                    <li><span class="file">home.json</span></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="features" class="section section-accent">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Ship content like you ship code")}</h2>
    <p class="muted lead reveal">
      {gettext(
        "Glossia borrows proven patterns from software engineering and applies them to content workflows, so you can ship content with the same confidence you ship code."
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="feature-icon violet">#</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Incremental updates")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "We use lockfiles and DAG graphs to update only what changed, so you skip redundant work and save both time and money on every run."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="feature-icon amber">&#10003;</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Linting and validation")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "The same idea behind CI checks: run syntax validators, linters, and custom commands against every output before it lands."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="feature-icon green">&#187;</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Retry on failure")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "When a check fails, agents see the error and try again. Automatic retries with feedback, the same pattern behind resilient distributed systems."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="feature-icon violet">&#182;</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Human feedback loop")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Reviewers flag issues through pull requests and update context files. Each correction feeds back into the next run, so the output gets closer to your voice with every cycle."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="refinement" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Progressive Refinement")}</h2>
    <p class="muted lead reveal">
      {gettext(
        "Outputs don't have to be perfect on day one. Like code, they improve through iteration."
      )}
    </p>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">01</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Draft")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "The LLM generates a structurally valid first pass from your context files. Formatting, code blocks, and frontmatter come through intact so the output is ready to review, not rebuild."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">02</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Review")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Your team flags issues through pull requests, just like code review. Reviewers comment on tone, accuracy, or missing nuance, and those notes become input for the next cycle."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">03</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Refine")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Updated context and glossary corrections feed into the next run. Every edit to a context file or glossary entry tightens the instructions the agent follows, so repeated mistakes disappear."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature reveal" data-interactive>
        <div class="step-number">04</div>
        <h3>{gettext("Converge")}</h3>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "Each cycle narrows the gap. The system learns your product's voice. Over time, outputs need fewer corrections and start matching the quality your team would produce by hand."
          )}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("FAQ")}</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details class="card faq-item reveal">
        <summary>{gettext("Why build this now?")}</summary>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "For the first time in history, we have tools that can capture context and interact with the outside world to produce and transform content across languages. LLMs changed what is possible, but possibility alone is not enough. You need a system that orchestrates those capabilities reliably: hashing to avoid redundant work, validation to catch errors, and retries to close the loop. On top of that, we build experiences for humans to review, correct, and enhance the system over time. That is what we are building from first principles and from years of experience building developer experiences and localization systems."
          )}
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="card faq-item reveal">
        <summary>{gettext("Do I need to bring my own models?")}</summary>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "No. Glossia acts as a broker between your content and the models. We work with linguists to understand which models perform best at certain tasks and define those defaults for you, so you get the best experience combining the models, the system, and your context. The landscape is moving fast, and you want the flexibility to switch models quickly without rewiring your pipeline. Glossia gives you strong defaults out of the box while keeping the freedom to override with any provider you prefer."
          )}
        </p>
      </details>
      <details class="card faq-item reveal">
        <summary>{gettext("Where do humans participate?")}</summary>
        <p>
          {gettext(
            "We are building experiences where humans take part in the agentic loops through interfaces that run in the browser or on the go. Implementation details like tools, models, and environments are abstracted away so reviewers can focus on the content itself. We are also designing agentic experiences for linguists to contribute directly to the system, refining voice, glossary, and quality standards without needing to touch config files or code."
          )}
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="blog" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="reveal">{gettext("Updates")}</h2>
    <div class="blog-list">
      <article :for={post <- @posts} class="card blog-card reveal" data-interactive>
        <a href={~p"/blog/#{post.slug}"}>
          <div class="blog-card-author">
            <img src={post.author.avatar} alt={post.author.name} class="blog-card-avatar" />
            <span class="blog-card-name">{post.author.name}</span>
            <span class="meta">{GlossiaWeb.BlogHTML.format_date(post.date)}</span>
          </div>
          <h3>{post.title}</h3>
          <p class="summary">{post.summary}</p>
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
